7430 Digital Labs

IoT Experimentation In The Wild

Developer: Adedayo Adebiyi 

The Problem Statement

At 7430 Digital Labs we have a platform that manages our Digital Out of Home Signage Media Players. The Media Players are based on custom IoT software deployed on to Raspberry PI Players.

Installers in the field always ran into the issue of connecting the Raspberry PIs to the Wifi network of the installation site, the reason being

  • The Raspberry PI is not aware of the current network it should connect to
  • The Raspberry PI cannot be connected to with keyboard and other input peripherals to enable setting up a Wifi Connection.
  • The Raspberry PI is not connected to a visual display yet.

The Solution

The BLE Wifi Connect Application

The BLE Wifi Connect Application is an application written in node and utilizes the bleno node library and node-wifi library to accomplish two things

1. The node-wifi is used in a wifi service that scans for available wireless networks that the Raspberry PI can see. The wifi service has functionality to connect to a wifi network and disconnect, it also can return the ssid of the currently connected to network

2. The Application starts a BLE broadcast that exposes 2 writeable properties for the Wifi Network SSID and Password.

3. The Application is written to using a tool like Light Blue Explorer, a BLE development testing tool
